{{Infobox philosopher | name = Martin van Hees | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | other_names = | birth_name = Martin Vinzenz Baldur Paul Maria van Hees | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1964|07|26}} | birth_place = [[Beilen]], [[The Netherlands]] | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | death_place = | death_cause = | residence = | nationality = [[The Netherlands|Dutch]] | era = | region = | religion = | school_tradition = | main_interests = [[Ethics]] | books = | alma_mater = [[Radboud University Nijmegen]] | institutions = [[VU University Amsterdam]] | notable_ideas = | influences = | influenced = | awards = | signature = | signature_alt = | signature_size = | website = {{official website|http://www.uva.nl/en/about-the-uva/organisation/staff-members/content/h/e/m.v.b.p.m.vanhees/m.v.b.p.m.van-hees.html}} }} '''Martin Vinzenz Baldur Paul Maria (Martin) van Hees''' (born 26 July 1964 in [[Beilen]]) is a [[The Netherlands|Dutch]] [[philosopher]].
Van Hees was professor of [[ethics]] at the [[University of Groningen]] and since April 2013 professor of political theory at the [[University of Amsterdam]]. He received a VICI-grant from the Netherlands Organisation for Scientific Research (NWO) to further research and develop the program ''Modelling Freedom: Formal Analysis and Normative Philosophy''. Van Hees is a vegetarian.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.geocities.com/ongehoordnl/achtergr.html|publisher=Ongehoord - actiegroep voor dierenwelzijn on [[Geocities.com]]|title=De veganist is het slechte geweten van de vegetariër - Interview met Martin van Hees|language=Dutch|accessdate=1 May 2008|archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/query?url=http://www.geocities.com/ongehoordnl/achtergr.html&date=2009-10-26+00:01:21|archivedate=26 October 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nwo.nl/nwohome.nsf/pages/NWOP_5W2L4K |language=Dutch |accessdate=1 May 2008 |publisher=[[:nl:Nederlandse Organisatie voor Wetenschappelijk Onderzoek|NWO]] |title=Toekenningen Vici 2003 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070608162152/http://www.nwo.nl/nwohome.nsf/pages/NWOP_5W2L4K |archivedate=8 June 2007 |df= }}</ref>
In August 2014, Van Hees will start a professorship of Ethics at [[VU University Amsterdam]].<ref name=Professorship>{{cite news|title=Martin van Hees per augustus 2014 hoogleraar Ethiek|url=http://www.vu.nl/nl/nieuws-agenda/nieuws/2014/jan-mrt/martin-van-hees-per-augustus-2014-hoogleraar-ethiek.asp|accessdate=12 June 2014|publisher=Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam (VU University Amsterdam)|date=25 February 2014|language=Dutch}}</ref> He is also a senior editor of the journal ''Economics and Philosophy''.<ref name=E&P>{{cite web|title=Economics and Philosophy: Editorial board|url=http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayMoreInfo?jid=EAP&type=eb|publisher=Cambridge Journals|accessdate=12 June 2014}}</ref> Since 2016 Van Hees is serving as Dean of the John Stuart Mill College of the VU Amsterdam and programme director for the VU's recently established Philosophy, Politics & Economics Bachelor's programme.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://vu-ppe.nl/faculty/martin-van-hees/|title=Prof. Martin van Hees {{!}} John Stuart Mill College|work=John Stuart Mill College|access-date=2017-09-13|language=en-US}}</ref>
== Education == After receiving degrees in political science and philosophy at the [[Erasmus University]] in Rotterdam, Van Hees obtained his PhD in social sciences at the [[Radboud University Nijmegen]] in 1994 with the dissertation: ''Rights, liberalism and social choice: a logical and game-theoretical analysis of individual and collective rights.''<ref>{{cite book | last = Hees | first = Martin | title = Rights, liberalism and social choice: a logical and game-theoretical analysis of individual and collective rights | publisher = Nijmegen | location = Amsterdam | year = 1994 | isbn = 9789090075914 }}</ref>
Van Hees became a member of the [[Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences]] in 2013.<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.knaw.nl/en/members/members/14314 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160131211413/https://www.knaw.nl/en/members/members/14314 |title=Martin van Hees |publisher=Royal Netherlands Academy of Arts and Sciences |date= |archive-date=31 January 2016 |accessdate=31 January 2016}}</ref>
